Jenni Evans, News24Buyisiwe Dashe (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The father of the three-year-old girl who went missing during flash floods two weeks ago said he blamed himself. WATCHWelkom -&nbsp;Free State police need help in finding a woman who went missing in Welkom on Friday. Buyisiwe Dashe, 37, was with her husband David at the Boitumelo Mall in Thabong, Welkom at noon on Friday.The couple spoke again by phone at around 14:00 and that is the last her worried husband heard from her, Captain Stephen Thakeng said. They had not argued, and he has tried without any success to raise her on the phone after that. She did not come home, and has been reported missing at Riebeeckstad satellite police station. A police hunt for her was underway on Saturday. Anybody with information of her whereabouts is asked to call Constable Poloko Mphatane on 057 3881 000 during office hours.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.